.TH CPRINTF 1 "2025" "cprintf 2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cprintf \- formatted output with colors and text effects
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cprintf
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I format
[\fIarguments\fR...]
.br
.B echo
.I text
|
.B cprintf
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cprintf
is a printf-compatible utility that processes XML-style markup tags for colors and text formatting. It supports nested tags, inline modifiers, multiple color spaces (standard, high intensity, 8-bit, 24-bit), and all standard printf format specifiers.
.PP
When used as a library (sourced), the
.B cprintf
function can be called directly from bash scripts.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.B \-\-check\-color\-support
Check terminal color support and display capabilities (8, 16, 256, 24Bit)
.TP
.B \-\-supported\-tags
Display all supported tags with examples
.TP
.B \-\-color\-codes
Display color code reference with all notation formats
.SH MARKUP TAGS
.SS Text Formatting Tags
.TP
.B <b></b>
Bold text
.TP
.B <i></i>
Italic text
.TP
.B <u></u>
Underlined text
.TP
.B <dim></dim>
Dim/faint text
.TP
.B <inv></inv>
Inverted colors (swap foreground/background)
.TP
.B <hidden></hidden>
Hidden/invisible text
.TP
.B <strike></strike>
Strikethrough text
.TP
.B <blink></blink>
Blinking text
.SS Color Tags
.TP
.B <fg:\fIcolor\fB></fg>
Set foreground color
.TP
.B <bg:\fIcolor\fB></bg>
Set background color
.PP
Colors can be specified using multiple notations (see COLOR NOTATION section).
.SH COLOR NOTATION
.SS Decimal Numbers
.TP
.B 0-7
Standard colors (black, red, green, yellow, blue, magenta, cyan, white)
.TP
.B 9
Terminal default color
.TP
.B 16-255
8-bit extended color palette
.TP
.B 256+
24-bit true colors (RGB as decimal value)
.SS @ Prefix (Explicit Extended/True Color)
.TP
.B @0-@255
8-bit extended colors
.TP
.B @256+
24-bit true colors
.SS # Prefix (Hex Notation)
.TP
.B #0-#7
Standard colors (single hex digit)
.TP
.B #8-#F
High intensity colors (single hex digit)
.TP
.B #00-#FF
8-bit extended colors (two hex digits)
.TP
.B #RRGGBB
24-bit true colors (six hex digits, RGB format)
.SS Color Name Aliases
.TP
.B lowercase
Standard colors: black, red, green, yellow, blue, magenta, cyan, white
.TP
.B Capitalized
High intensity colors: Black, Red, Green, Yellow, Blue, Magenta, Cyan, White
.SH INLINE MODIFIERS
Modifiers can be appended to color specifications to add effects or change intensity:
.TP
.B +
Increase intensity (standard→high, high→bold, 8-bit/24-bit→bold)
.TP
.B \-
Decrease intensity (high→standard, any→dim)
.TP
.B !
Bold effect
.TP
.B *
Italic effect
.TP
.B _
Underline effect
.TP
.B =
Strikethrough effect
.TP
.B ~
Invert effect
.PP
Multiple modifiers can be combined, e.g., <fg:red!*_> for bold italic underlined red.
.SH INTENSITY MODIFIER BEHAVIOR
.TP
.B Standard Colors (0-7)
+ → High intensity color
.br
\- → Dim effect
.TP
.B High Intensity Colors (8-15)
+ → Bold effect
.br
\- → Standard color
.TP
.B 8-Bit Colors (16-255)
+ → Bold effect
.br
\- → Dim effect
.TP
.B 24-Bit Colors (256+)
+ → Bold effect
.br
\- → Dim effect
.SH HTML ENTITIES
The following HTML entities are supported for literal characters:
.TP
.B &lt;
< (less than)
.TP
.B &gt;
> (greater than)
.TP
.B &amp;
& (ampersand)
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Usage
.PP
.nf
cprintf "<fg:red>Error:</fg> File not found\\n"
cprintf "<b>Bold</b> and <i>italic</i> text\\n"
cprintf "<fg:blue><u>Underlined blue text</u></fg>\\n"
.fi
.SS Color Notations
.PP
.nf
# Standard colors
cprintf "<fg:red>Red text</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:1>Red text (code)</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:#1>Red text (hex)</fg>\\n"

# High intensity
cprintf "<fg:Red>Bright red</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:red+>Bright red (modifier)</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:#9>Bright red (hex)</fg>\\n"

# 8-bit colors
cprintf "<fg:196>Bright red (8-bit)</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:@196>Bright red (@prefix)</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:#C4>Bright red (hex)</fg>\\n"

# 24-bit true colors
cprintf "<fg:#FF6B6B>Custom red</fg>\\n"
.fi
.SS Inline Modifiers
.PP
.nf
cprintf "<fg:red!>Bold red</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:green*>Italic green</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:blue_>Underlined blue</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:yellow~>Inverted yellow</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:red!*_>Bold italic underlined red</fg>\\n"
.fi
.SS Nested Tags
.PP
.nf
cprintf "<fg:red>Red <b>bold</b> text</fg>\\n"
cprintf "<bg:yellow><fg:black>Black on yellow</fg></bg>\\n"
cprintf "<fg:blue><b><u>Bold underlined blue</u></b></fg>\\n"
.fi
.SS Printf Formatting
.PP
.nf
cprintf "<fg:red>Error:</fg> <b>%s</b>\\n" "File not found"
cprintf "<fg:green>Success:</fg> Processed <b>%d</b> items\\n" 42
cprintf "<fg:blue>Progress:</fg> %.2f%% complete\\n" 75.5
.fi
.SS Piped Input
.PP
.nf
echo "<fg:red>Error message</fg>" | cprintf
cat file.txt | cprintf
.fi
.SS Library Usage
.PP
.nf
#!/bin/bash
source /usr/local/bin/cprintf

cprintf "<fg:green>Success:</fg> %s\\n" "Operation completed"
cprintf "<fg:red!><b>ERROR:</b></fg> %s\\n" "Failed to connect"
.fi
.SH COLOR SPACES
.SS Standard Colors (0-7)
8 basic colors supported by all terminals:
.br
0=black, 1=red, 2=green, 3=yellow, 4=blue, 5=magenta, 6=cyan, 7=white
.SS High Intensity Colors (8-15)
Bright versions of standard colors:
.br
8-15 or use + modifier with standard colors
.SS 8-Bit Extended Colors (16-255)
256-color palette:
.br
16-231: 6×6×6 RGB cube
.br
232-255: Grayscale ramp
.SS 24-Bit True Colors (16,777,216 colors)
Full RGB color support using #RRGGBB notation or decimal values 256+
.SH TERMINAL SUPPORT
Most modern terminals support standard, high intensity, and 8-bit colors. True color (24-bit) support varies by terminal.
.PP
Check your terminal's capabilities:
.PP
.nf
cprintf --check-color-support
.fi
